[{"id":34026,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["one point","two points","three points","four points"],"answer":1,"solution":"Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">R</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">R</mi></math>&nbsp;be functions defined by<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mtd><mtd><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd><mtd><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\" columnspacing=\"1.4ex\"><mtr><mtd><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>After taking intersection we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</p><p>Now, checking continuity at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>We get,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Hence, discontinuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>And,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Hence, discontinuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33992,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["968","1152","746","1250"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\lim _{x \\rightarrow 0} f(x)=a \\ln 2 \\ln 3 \\\\ & \\lim _{n \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{72^x-9^x-8^x+1}{\\sqrt{2}-\\sqrt{1+\\cos x}}=\\lim _{x \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\left(8^x-1\\right)\\left(9^x-1\\right)}{\\sqrt{2}-\\sqrt{1+\\cos x}} \\\\ & \\lim _{n \\rightarrow 0}\\left(\\frac{8^x-1}{x}\\right)\\left(\\frac{9^x-1}{x}\\right)\\left(\\frac{x^2}{1-\\cos x}\\right)(\\sqrt{2}+\\sqrt{1+\\cos x}) \\\\ & \\therefore \\ln 8 \\times \\ln 9 \\times 2 \\times 2 \\sqrt{2}=24 \\sqrt{2} \\ln 2 \\ln 3 \\\\ & \\therefore a=24 \\sqrt{2}, a^2=576 \\times 2=1152\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":33980,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["$64$","$72$","$48$","$36$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}<br/>& f\\left(0^{-}\\right)=\\mathrm{e}^{\\lim _{x \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\mathrm{ax}}{\\mathrm{x}}}=\\mathrm{e}^{\\mathrm{a}} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{f}(0)=1+\\mathrm{b} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{f}\\left(0^{+}\\right)=\\frac{\\frac{1}{2 \\sqrt{\\mathrm{x}+4}}}{\\frac{1}{3}(\\mathrm{x}+\\mathrm{c})^{-\\frac{2}{3}}}=\\frac{\\frac{1}{2(2)}}{\\frac{1}{3} \\cdot \\mathrm{c}^{-\\frac{2}{3}}} \\\\\n& =\\frac{3}{4} \\mathrm{c}^{2 / 3}<br/>\\end{aligned}$<br/>Also at $\\mathrm{x}=0$;<br/>$c^{1 / 3}=2 \\Rightarrow c=8$<br/>So $\\mathrm{f}\\left(0^{+}\\right)=\\frac{3}{4}(8)^{2 / 3}=3$<br/>Now, $\\mathrm{e}^{\\mathrm{a}}=\\mathrm{b}+1=3$<br/>$\\mathrm{e}^{\\mathrm{a}} . \\mathrm{b} \\cdot \\mathrm{c}=3 \\cdot 2 \\cdot 8=48$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34062,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><br />Differentiating two times.<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#34;</mo></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"\"><mtable columnalign=\"right left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#34;</mo></msup><mfenced><msup><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#34;</mo></msup><mfenced><msup><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34040,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>min</mi><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>So, the graph of the function is&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aa4f9dee-c4a5-4336-8b9e-4cd3ab8d6faa-image.png\" style=\"width: 289px; height: 129px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b92dee34-e409-4a53-9b7f-857722830bbd-image.png\" style=\"width: 325px; height: 130px;\" /></p><p>From the graph we can say that the function is continuous at all points in the interval&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>.</mo></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Again, from the diagram, we can say that at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;there are sharp edges.</p><p>So, the function is non differentiable at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34018,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mn>0</mn></mfenced></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Now for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo></mrow></munder><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>Now again rewriting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>or</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>&#8734;</mo></mrow></munder><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable equalcolumns=\"true\" equalrows=\"true\"><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>if</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>if</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>So <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is discontinuous at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>So <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> is discontinuous at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34032,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Here both the modulus function is continuous in its domain.</p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>Hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is continuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></munder><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is discontinuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>For&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is discontinuous when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>/</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>i.e when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mrow><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de9e46e8-f87d-44d9-b10e-cc06196ceee8-image.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 221px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":33986,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$f(x)$ is continuous and differentiable\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { at } x=1, \\mathrm{LHL}=\\mathrm{RHL}, \\mathrm{LHD}=\\mathrm{RHD} \\\\\n& -3 a-2=a^2+b,-6 a=b \\\\\n& a=2 ; b=-12 \\\\\n& f(x)=\\left\\{\\begin{array}{cc}\n-6 x^2-2, & x < 1 \\\\\n4-12 x, & x \\geq 1\n\\end{array}\\right.\n\\end{aligned}$<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cH2y87Qs33gJnKyjgjIsHWd143usH7znLTX-mL0kNuE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\left.\\text { Area }=\\int_{-\\sqrt{3}}^1\\left(-6 x^2-2+20\\right) d x+\\int_1^2(4-12 x+20) d x\\right] \\\\ & =16+12 \\sqrt{3}+6=22+12 \\sqrt{3} \\\\ & \\therefore \\quad \\alpha+\\beta=34\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (22 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34009,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is differentiable at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, so function must be continuous at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, hence</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LHL</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>RHL</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>So,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Putting in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>k</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>So,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>12</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>96</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>103</mn><mn>96</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>103</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>So,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>103</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn><msqrt><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>103</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>309</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34063,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is differentiable then will also continuous then&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>&#960;</mi></mfenced><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8230;</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is continuous.</p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mrow><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mrow><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>sin</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>then,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mi>&#960;</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Similarly,&nbsp;we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"\" open=\"{\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>As the function is twice differentiable, the second-order derivatives, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>D</mi></math>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>'</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mfenced><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos&#960;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>)</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":33975,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["4","1","2","0"],"answer":2,"solution":"Note $2\\sin|x|\\cos|x| = \\sin(2|x|)$.<br>For $x > 0$: $f(x) = a + x - \\frac{\\sin 2x}{x} \\xrightarrow{x \\to 0^+} a - 2$.<br>For $x < 0$: $f(x) = -a + x + \\frac{\\sin 2x}{x} \\xrightarrow{x \\to 0^-} -a + 2$.<br>For continuity: $a - 2 = 2 - a \\Rightarrow a = 2$, and $b = a - 2 = 0$.<br>$a + b = 2$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":34005,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mi>R</mi></math></p><p>Now using the property of greatest integer function and&nbsp;simplifying the function we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msqrt><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p><p>Now plotting the diagram we get,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b6c78f72-2e3a-4af6-9cb4-16130816aa9e.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 223px;\" /></p><p>Now from the diagram we can say that,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is discontinuous at two points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mrow><mo>&#8211;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":34112,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["Statement-1 is true, Statement-2 is true; Statement-2 is not the correct explanation for Statement-1","Statement-1 is true, Statement-2 is false","Statement-1 is false, Statement-2 is true","Statement-1 is true, Statement-2 is true; Statement-2 is the correct explanation for Statement-1"],"answer":3,"solution":"$f(x)=\\frac{1}{e^x+2 e^{-x}}=\\frac{e^x}{e^{2 x}+2}$\n$f^{\\prime}(x)=\\frac{\\left(e^{2 x}+2\\right) e^x-2 e^{2 x} \\cdot e^x}{\\left(e^{2 x+2}\\right)^2}$\n$f^{\\prime}(x)=0 \\quad \\Rightarrow e^{2 x}+2=2 e^{2 x}$\n$\\mathrm{e}^{2 \\mathrm{x}}=2 \\quad \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{e}^{\\mathrm{x}}=\\sqrt{2}$\nmaximum $f(x)=\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{4}=\\frac{1}{2 \\sqrt{2}}$\n$0 < f(x) \\leq \\frac{1}{2 \\sqrt{2}} \\quad \\forall x \\in R$\nSince $0 < \\frac{1}{3} < \\frac{1}{2 \\sqrt{2}} \\quad \\Rightarrow$ for some $c \\in R$\n$f(c)=\\frac{1}{3}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2010","image":null},{"id":33979,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Continuity and Differentiability","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$f(x)=\\left\\{\\begin{array}{cc}<br/>x, & x \\lt -1 \\\\\nx^{21}, & -1 \\leq x \\lt 0 \\\\\nx, & 0 \\leq x \\lt 1 \\\\\nx^{21}, & x \\geq 1<br/>\\end{array}\\right.$<br/>$f(x)$ is continuous everywhere.<br/>$\\begin{aligned}<br/>& \\therefore \\mathrm{n}=0 \\\\\n& \\mathrm{f}^{\\prime}(\\mathrm{x})=\\left\\{\\begin{array}{cc}<br/>1, & \\mathrm{x} \\lt -1 \\\\\n21 \\mathrm{x}^{20}, & -1 \\leq \\mathrm{x} \\lt 0 \\\\\n1, & 0 \\lt \\mathrm{x} \\lt 1 \\\\\n21 \\mathrm{x}^{20}, & \\mathrm{x} \\geq 1<br/>\\end{array}\\right.<br/>\\end{aligned}$<br/>$\\therefore \\mathrm{f}(\\mathrm{x})$ is non-differentiable at $\\mathrm{x}=-1,0,1$<br/>$\\begin{aligned}<br/>& \\therefore \\mathrm{m}=3 \\\\\n& \\mathrm{~m}+\\mathrm{n}=3<br/>\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null}]